node.text:
We are witnessing a planetary crisis unfold in real time.

Wildfires, floods: it’s never been clearer that our relationship with nature is broken. So where do we go from here? 👇 #WWFUntangled

We need to start working WITH nature instead of AGAINST nature. Nature-based solutions harness the power of the natural world in a way that benefits us and all life on this planet. 🌍

Did you know that, if all mangroves were lost or destroyed, 15 million more people would be affected by floods across the world each year? 

And that forests provide clean air and water, protect against erosion and landslides, and help to regulate the climate by removing carbon from the atmosphere? 🌊🌲

The natural world does so much to sustain and protect us. We must do more to help it thrive, and we must do it now. Double tap if you agree!

#NaturePositive #WWF #Biodiversity #Climate #ClimateChange #GlobalWarming #ClimateCrisis #ClimateAction #SaveThePlanet  #NoPlanetB #ClimateChangeIsReal #ClimateStrike #ClimateEmergency #ClimateJustice

node.text:
Meet Dominika @dominikamilek_wildlife, our Nature Photographer of September! She is a Polish photographer based in Reykjavík, Iceland. Her adventure with photography started around three years ago. 

She says about her love for wildlife photography: "Wildlife has been my biggest love since I can remember and I’m always down to explore every corner of our incredible world to encounter and photograph animals, who call these places home. 

"We often forget that we are part of nature, that we share feelings and cognitive abilities with other inhabitants of this world, and nature is what sustains us. At the end of the day, our life doesn’t exist outside the laws of nature. Just like the existence of all beings on Earth. 

“As Sir David Attenborough said: ‘Our planet is headed for disaster. We need to learn how to work with nature rather than against it.’ There are many easy ways to help the environment every day, like avoiding food waste, buying things second-hand, fixing stuff instead of buying new, and so on. These are small steps that we all can take in our own lives and set an example for others around us. After all, only by making a concerted effort will we have a chance of reversing the damage we have done to our planet."

node.text:
The Atlantic forest is a lush, rich place essential to the survival of local communities and home to precious species you can’t find anywhere else on Earth. 🌲🐛🦋🐆 Yet this forest - like so many others around the globe - is in danger - less than 20% of original forest remains. Thankfully, leaders are taking action. After endorsing the #LeadersPledge4Nature, Paraguay has extended a law for zero deforestation of the Atlantic forest - this is HUGE! 👏

Decision-makers in Paraguay are taking steps in the right direction, helping us build a future where there is more nature tomorrow than there is today. A future where people and nature thrive. And other leaders must do the same. 
 
This week, representatives and leaders from 193 countries are taking to #UNGA76 to discuss some of the most pressing issues of our time - such as nature loss and the climate crisis. It's crucial that they come together to inspire further action for our planet. 👉 Double tap if you agree and head to the link in our bio to learn more! #TheRaceIsOn for a #NaturePositive world by 2030 🌍

#Climate #ClimateChange #GlobalWarming #ClimateCrisis #ClimateAction #SaveThePlanet  #NoPlanetB #ClimateChangeIsReal #ClimateStrike #ClimateEmergency #ClimateJustice #WWF #Wildlife

⚠️The cost of plastic is higher than you might think⚠️

We are witnessing a planetary crisis unfold in real time.

Wildfires, floods: it’s never been clearer that our relationship with nature is broken. So where do we go from here? 👇 #WWFUntangled

We need to start working WITH nature instead of AGAINST nature. Nature-based solutions harness the power of the natural world in a way that benefits us and all life on this planet. 🌍

Did you know that, if all mangroves were lost or destroyed, 15 million more people would be affected by floods across the world each year? 

And that forests provide clean air and water, protect against erosion and landslides, and help to regulate the climate by removing carbon from the atmosphere? 🌊🌲

The natural world does so much to sustain and protect us. We must do more to help it thrive, and we must do it now. Double tap if you agree!

#NaturePositive #WWF #Biodiversity #Climate #ClimateChange #GlobalWarming #ClimateCrisis #ClimateAction #SaveThePlanet  #NoPlanetB #ClimateChangeIsReal #ClimateStrike #ClimateEmergency #ClimateJustice

This urgent question requires an urgent solution, and this week’s #IUCNWorldCongress looks at how we can tackle it together. 

The #IUCNWorldCongress this year comes at a crucial time⏳ It’s happening ahead of important UN decision-making meetings on climate, nature loss, and food systems. 

And these decisions guide humanity’s relationship with our planet for the decades ahead. We MUST address nature loss and the #ClimateCrisis, and send a reminder to Governments that #TheRaceIsOn to turn the tide now. Tap the link in our bio to learn more!
